current_subtask:
  summary: Third pass. Derived a predictive cadence model from timestamps across all three passes and confirmed the wave-assembly mechanism directly (shard PRs land against the wave branch, not main). Deploying read-only verification subagents this pass per explicit instruction, scoped to analysis only - no code, no comments, no merges, no new branches.
  predicted_cadence:
    - "issues spawn in bursts of 4-5 within under 2 minutes, ~12-18 min gaps between bursts"
    - "leaf PRs land sequentially, one per ~5-13 min, accelerating toward the end of a backlog"
    - "once a parent's full leaf set is open, convergence issues appear within ~8 min and their wave PRs within ~2-3 min more"
    - "each wave PR is built via a chain of shard PRs based on the wave branch itself (not main): one main-sync shard, then one shard per leaf branch folded in, ~1-2 min apart"
  subagent_deployment: read-only verification only - cross-checking each leaf PR's diff against its issue's declared Reserved scope for hidden file overlaps that could break wave assembly, and independently re-deriving CI status for lanes not yet directly checked. No subagent had write/comment/merge/push tools for this repository.
  subagent_findings: verified (not speculative) collisions across #140,143,148,149,150,151 - three-way anchor conflict in social-postgres-community-runtime.mjs, two independent package.json line conflicts (test:social, test:social:postgres), and a semantic collision where #151's moderate() drops #149's self-ban/peer-moderator-ban hierarchy guard on naive merge. Wave #154 already resolved an analogous undeclared package.json (test:remote) collision between #145/#147. #141 ships scripts/authority-manifest-core.mjs (356 lines) outside its own self-declared scope. #144's workflow-permission claims were independently verified true against the actual diff.
